## Description

@pub-sub-loop-transport · P3 · In Review · Claude-C

### Problem: raw `tensor_parallel` API in transport layer

The transport layer currently exposes two functions from the legacy `tensor_parallel` namespace that operate on individual state collections:

```cpp
// Current: legacy tensor_parallel namespace
namespace tensor_parallel {
    // Remove individuals from a state collection by value equality
    template <typename ForwardIt, typename T>
    ForwardIt erase(ForwardIt first, ForwardIt last, const T& value);

    // Remove individuals from a state collection by predicate
    template <typename ForwardIt, typename Pred>
    ForwardIt erase_if(ForwardIt first, ForwardIt last, Pred pred);
}
```

These are used by the transport layer to evict dead individuals from channel subscriber lists and to prune stale state entries from history caches. They should be migrated to the `world::std` namespace and adapted to work with individual-aware containers.

### Proposed migration

```cpp
namespace world::std {

// Erase individual entries from a pub/sub channel subscriber list
// Difference from standard erase: emits a `SubscriberEvicted` event
// to the profiler for each removed individual
template <typename Container, typename T>
auto erase(Container& c, const T& value) -> typename Container::size_type {
    auto count = ::std::erase(c, value);
    if (count > 0) {
        profiler::emit(SubscriberEvicted{.channel = c.channel_id(), .count = count});
    }
    return count;
}

// Erase individual entries by predicate
// Common predicates:
//   is_dead(id) — individual no longer exists in the world
//   is_stale(entry, max_age) — state entry older than max_age ticks
//   is_unreachable(id) — individual's node is unreachable via transport
template <typename Container, typename Pred>
auto erase_if(Container& c, Pred pred) -> typename Container::size_type {
    auto count = ::std::erase_if(c, pred);
    if (count > 0) {
        profiler::emit(SubscribersEvicted{.channel = c.channel_id(), .count = count});
    }
    return count;
}

}  // namespace world::std
```

### Usage in transport layer

```cpp
// Before (legacy):
tensor_parallel::erase_if(subscriber_list.begin(), subscriber_list.end(),
    [&](const SubscriberEntry& e) { return !world.is_alive(e.individual_id); });

// After (migrated):
world::std::erase_if(subscriber_list,
    [&](const SubscriberEntry& e) { return !world.is_alive(e.individual_id); });
// Also emits profiler event for monitoring subscriber churn
```

### Backward compatibility

Add `using` declarations in the old namespace:

```cpp
namespace tensor_parallel {
    // Deprecated — use world::std::erase / world::std::erase_if
    using world::std::erase;
    using world::std::erase_if;
}
```

